text.tspan: Share of population with alcohol or drug use disorders, male vs. female, 2016
Alcohol or drug use dependence is defined by the International Classification of Diseases as the presence of three or
more indicators of dependence for at least a month within the previous year. This is given as the age-standardized
prevalence for comparison by sex, country and through time. Tobacco smoking is not included.
Share of females with alcohol or drug use disorders
Share of males with alcohol or drug use disorders
Source: IHME, Global Burden of Disease (GBD)
